race.comment: DERVINIA (13) win record hardly excites and worth noting her lone victory came at this track. Chased right though the line when a narrow second over 1400m at Bathurst. Well placed back to the 1200m. Go close. CHAPPOLICIOUS (7) lightly raced filly rewarded for her consistency at start four when a sharp Maiden winner over 1100m at Wellington. Maps well today and no shock to see her fight this out. SUPREME STYLE (3) knuckled down strongly to get within a long neck of the winner in third last start over 1100m at Wellington. Tough to stop again. INVINCIBLE SALEX (5) comes up with a decent marble at start three with the claim. Went back from the outside draw and never in the contest when seventh over 1000m at Orange. Trained on the track and can bounce back.
